commit.message:
Support libidn installed with pkg-config support

If compilation / linking information is provided by pkg-config, then use
the information.  Homebrew (and other package managers) will install
pkg-config information, so we don't need to specify compilation info
when installing the gem.

With this change I can just do `rake compile` on Apple Silicon without
manually specifying the installation location of libidn

Support libidn installed with pkg-config support

If compilation / linking information is provided by pkg-config, then use
the information.  Homebrew (and other package managers) will install
pkg-config information, so we don't need to specify compilation info
when installing the gem.

With this change I can just do `rake compile` on Apple Silicon without
manually specifying the installation location of libidn

commit.message:
Use ruby xmalloc/xrealloc for local allocations

Documentation for xfree indicates that it must only be used with pointers
allocated from its corresponding allocators: Ruby makes no guarantee that xfree
will be the same as free.

will be the same as free.

commit.message:
Use idn_free for libidn-allocated strings

Libidn is not guaranteed to use the same allocator as Ruby, so it's not safe to
xfree strings that it allocates.
